sd.PT_NAME: Loss of personal independence in daily activities

freetext.SYMPTOMS_DESCRIPTION: Moderate - severe Chills without fever and goosebumps that won't go away for 4 days straight impacting sleep, working and daily activities and seek medical attention and testing
freetext.HEALTHCARE_VISITS_OTHER: I went to clinic x2, I have 8 other labs pending, but got tested asymptomatic and symptomatic for covid and influenza both negstive

freetext.SYSTEMIC_REACTION_OTHER: I had mod chills and fatigue 1/2/21-1/12/21, 5 negative covid tests, had to seek MD x2 in OP setting, had to miss 3 days of work, had reduced body temp and rigors at night from being so cold. You stopped letting me report. My c reactive protein was elevated in my labs.

Lower than normal temps 97.3-97.5 despite checking x3 different thermometers, my skin does not feel cold but I feel cold and am wearing many layers, chills are mild no shaking, feeling anxious about lower temps, marked feeling fair as this is not normal for me
Mild right back pain (prior history of kidney stones)
MildTingling radiating in fingers intermittently throughout day
Moderate Back Ache Right  kidney area (I have a prior history of kidney stones may be unrelated to vaccine)
